{"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeProtocol\/getWeekNumberingYear()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeprotocol\/getweeknumberingyear()"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeProtocol"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week-numbering year in which the week containing","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"datetime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" falls."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"getWeekNumberingYear","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This function, taken together with ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_date_time_get_week_of_year()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_get_day_of_week()"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used to determine the full ISO"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"week date on which "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"datetime"},{"text":" falls.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is usually equal to the normal Gregorian year (as returned by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_date_time_get_year()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"), except as detailed below:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For Thursday, the week-numbering year is always equal to the usual","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"calendar year.  For other days, the number is such that every day"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"within a complete week (Monday to Sunday) is contained within the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"same week-numbering year."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday occurring near the end of the year,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this may mean that the week-numbering year is one greater than the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calendar year (so that these days have the same week-numbering year"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as the Thursday occurring early in the next year).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For Friday, Saturday and Sunday occurring near the start of the year,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this may mean that the week-numbering year is one less than the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"calendar year (so that these days have the same week-numbering year"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as the Thursday occurring late in the previous year)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An equivalent description is that the week-numbering year is equal to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the calendar year containing the majority of the days in the current"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"week (Monday to Sunday).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that January 1 0001 in the proleptic Gregorian calendar is a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Monday, so this function never returns 0.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"title":"getWeekNumberingYear()","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"getWeekNumberingYear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib16DateTimeProtocolPAAE20getWeekNumberingYearSiyF","extendedModule":"GLib"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeProtocol/getWeekNumberingYear()":{"title":"getWeekNumberingYear()","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week-numbering year in which the week containing","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"datetime"},{"type":"text","text":" falls."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeProtocol\/getWeekNumberingYear()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"getWeekNumberingYear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeprotocol\/getweeknumberingyear()","role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeProtocol":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeprotocol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DateTimeProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeProtocol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDateTime"},{"text":" is a structure that combines a Gregorian date and time","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"into a single structure.","type":"text"}],"title":"DateTimeProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DateTimeProtocol"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]}}}